			<ns0:name>dmichael@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/dmichael@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The Chrome integration bots determine which pepper to use for NaCl from the Chrome DEPS file, when they should be using the version specified in NaCl's DEPS file.

Here's the situation:
1. Some breaking change happens in pepper in Chrome. NaCl in the chrome tree still builds, however, because it builds against its own revision of pepper (specified in chromium/src/DEPS as nacl_chrome_ppapi_revision; currently this is 93192).

2. I roll DEPS in NaCl to get the latest pepper changes and update NaCl to deal with the changes.  At this point, you'd like to think the integration bots would be green if I did everything right.

3. However...  the integration bots do NOT grab the pepper version that is now referenced by NaCl. Instead, it takes top-of-tree NaCl code (which builds with the new pepper version at the revision listed in the NaCl DEPS file, in this case 93360) and builds this code against the version of pepper specified in the Chrome DEPS file by nacl_chrome_ppapi_revision (still 93192).
